rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These activities include a complex collection of shipping, storing, repairing and other similar activities that are industrial in nature. Passenger terminals are not included in this category.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Port, ship-building, and related activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This activity is characterized by electrical power generation, control facilities, distribution centers, etc. Use this category for any activity associated with power supply and distribution.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Power generation, control, monitor, or distribution activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Activities primarily associated with switching centers, transformer locations, and other power-related facilities that serve as storage or transit points in the distribution system.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Power generation, storage, or processing activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments are responsible for the construction of electric power and communication transmission lines and towers, radio and television towers, cable laying, and cable television lines.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Power lines, communication and transmission lines

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Establishments in this subcategory organize, promote, and manage live performing arts productions, sports events, and similar events, such as state fairs, county fairs, agricultural fairs, concerts, and festivals. They may operate their own facilities, such as arenas, stadiums, and theaters, or rent from others; or they may operate these facilities for rent to other promoters. Theatrical (except motion picture) booking agencies are included in this subcategory.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Promoter of performing arts, sports, and similar events

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Refers to the public entity that the property belongs to, or the public entity responsible for the property. Public entities are agencies from local, regional, state, or federal governments.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Public restrictions--local, state, and federal ownership

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Radio, TV, or wireless transmitter

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Use this category for identifying rail maintenance and storage activities, which are industrial in character, from rail movement and railroad rights-ofway. This category also includes railroad switching activities.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Rail maintenance, storage, or related activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Railroads, including monorails, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments rent or lease, and may additionally sell assets. Assets can be tangible (real estate or equipment) or intangible (patents and trademarks). This category's usefulness depends entirely on the activity and structure-type dimensions.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Real estate, and rental and leasing

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Large industrialized warehouse structures with specialized cold storage and climate control facilities.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Refrigerated warehouse or cold storage

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The road, ground passenger, and transit transportation category comprises a variety of passenger transportation functions, such as urban transit systems; chartered, school, and interurban bus transportation; and taxis. Establishment types primarily reflect the mode of transit utilized.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Road, ground passenger, and transit transportation

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Includes movable units that may or may not be permanently anchored.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Roadside stand, pushcarts, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments provide installation and services for roofing, siding, sheet metal, and roof drainage equipment, such as downspouts and gutters. Activities include treating roofs (i.e., by spraying, painting, or coating), copper smithing, tin smithing, installing skylights, installing metal ceilings, flashing, duct work, and capping.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Roofing, siding, and sheet metal contractors

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Although these activities are normally associated with bike paths, jogging trails, sidewalks, and such facilities, they also include the kinds that happen on athletic tracks and playgrounds. Exercising and aerobic activities include those that take place in health clubs and gymnasiums besides outdoor facilities.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Running, jogging, bicycling, aerobics, exercising, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This category includes activities associated with water and marine based travel, movement, and their related activities. Use the subcategories to distinguish areas of marine movement from marine storage activities.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sailing, boating, and other port, marine and water-based activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Scuba diving, snorkeling, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Activities primarily associated with linear features, such as pipelines, channels, etc., located in easements and point features, such as air vents, pumping stations, piping junctions, etc., that may or may not be in easements.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sewage storing, pumping, or piping

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Establishments in this subcategory collect, treat, and dispose of waste materials. Establishments locally haul waste materials; operate materials recovery facilities (i.e., sort recyclable materials from trash); provide remediation services (i.e., the cleanup of contaminated sites); operate sewer systems or sewage treatment facilities; or provide septic pumping or other miscellaneous waste management services. Establishments that primarily haul waste over long distances are classified in the transportation category.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sewer, solid waste, and related services

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This activity is characterized by sewer-related activities, such as pumping, piping, storing, treating, filtering, etc., whether urban or rural, private or public. Use this category for any activity associated with sewers.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sewer-related control, monitor, or distribution activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Use this category for all agricultural structures. For tracking specialized farm and agricultural structures, use the subcategories. This broad category also includes lumber mills, maple sugaring facilities (sugar camp, sugar bush, etc.), agricultural terraces (to hold water and allow infiltration), waterways and stabilized paths (to direct runoff), sediment basins (to hold silt), and fencing (mainly to reduce livestock density).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sheds, farm buildings, or agricultural facilities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This category captures all uses that are business related. Use it as a catch-all category for all retail, office, commercial, and industrial activities when the subcategories are either too specific or otherwise unknown (as in comprehensive plan designations).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Shopping, business, or trade activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments operate skating rinks; they may further offer skating products and services.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Skating rinks, roller skates, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This is a broad category that includes leisure sport activities on snow: skiing, luge, bobsled, toboggan.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Skiing, snowboarding, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Use this category for mass assembly of people for social (eg., city hall), cultural (eg., parades), or religious (eg. churches) purposes. It also includes large outdoor ceremonies for religious, cultural, or other purposes. Although such activities may occur infrequently and may not involve any functional or structural characteristics (for example a spontaneous gathering that occurs on an annual basis on a hilltop), identifying where mass assembling of people occurs is essential for many planning applications. Use this category to capture such use information. Often this may mean assigning a mass assembly category to areas that alread have other activity categories assigned. Apply this category when other more specific mass assembly categories are inappropriate.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Social, cultural, or religious assembly

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Use this category for all institutional activities. This broad category may also be used for land-use designations in comprehensive and general plans.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Social, institutional, or infrastructure-related activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments provide social assistance services directly to individuals. They do not offer residential or accommodation services.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Social assistance, welfare, and charitable services

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This classification comprises establishments that produce, distribute, or publish music and musical recordings, or provide sound recording and related services.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sound recording, production, publishing, and distribution

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Sporting goods are specialized clothing, equipment, accessories, and service establishments that retail for sport and recreational activities. They retail such goods as bicycles and bicycle parts, camping equipment, exercise and fitness equipment, athletic uniforms, specialty sports footwear, and similar equipment and accessories. Toy and hobby shops primarily retail toys, games, and hobby and craft supplies. Musical instrument establishments retail musical instruments and related supplies; a good example of such an establishment would be a piano store. Some of these establishments may also retail sheet music, offer music instruction, rent or repair instruments, but the primary product is the sale of instruments. Establishments selling sheet music along with books, magazines, etc. should be classified under the appropriate category and not here.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Sporting goods, toy and hobby, and musical instruments

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments perform crop protecting services, soil preparation activity, or crop production services. Activities include dusting, spraying, plowing, fertilizing, seed bed preparation, planting, and cultivating.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Spraying, dusting, and other related services

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These are parks designated by local, state, federal, or other speical jurisdictional agencies (such as tribal governments) whose development characteristics may vary widely--anything from natural state to fully developed facilities. They may also have structures and site features that are historic, cultural, religious, or archeological in significance. No matter how infreqent the use of these facilities or levels of development, use this category to classify park designations. See if one of the subcategories for specific state or national parks is appropriate. If not, use this category for all other parks.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: State, national, or other parks and recreational sites

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Not related to utilities, but may be related to an industrial or commercial enterprise. This may include tanks, tank farms, open storage, etc., above or below ground.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Storage of chemical, nuclear, or other materials

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Not related to utilities, but may be related to an industrial or commercial enterprise. This may include tanks, tank farms, open storage, etc., above or below ground.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Storage of natural gas, fuels, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Includes activities associated with lifeguard services and other related activities.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Swimming, diving, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These schools offer vocational and technical training in a variety of technical subjects and trades. The training often leads to job-specific certification. The individual classifications are based on the type of training provided.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Technical, trade, and other specialty schools

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Activities associated with telecommunications encompass communication tower facilities, antennae locations, repeater stations, and distribution centers.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Telecommunications-related control, monitor, or distribution activities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: For tracking the number of occupants, guest rooms, or beds, use additional attributes or fields in the land-use database.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Temporary structures, tents, etc. for shelter

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This subcategory comprises establishments producing live presentations by actors and actresses, singers, dancers, musicians, and other performing artists. Establishments include: companies, groups, or theaters that produce theatrical presentations and dance (ballet, musicals, operas, plays, etc.); dinner theaters that produce theatrical productions and provide food and beverage for consumption on the premises; and groups or freelance artists producing live musical entertainment. Theater/dance groups or companies may or may not operate their own theater or other facility for staging their shows. Musical groups and artists may perform in front of a live audience or in a studio, and may or may not operate their own facilities for staging their shows.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Theater, dance, or music establishment

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This includes activities associated with playing baseball, basketball, and other related games.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Track and field, team sports (baseball, basketball, etc.), or other sports

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This is a catch-all category comprising transportation, communication, and utilities for essential facilities. In this category, an establishment cannot be distinguished by a single physical location as it can in most other categories. To classify land in this category, other factors are needed for deciding which land serves a particular establishment. In most cases, the type of establishment in this category is easily deduced from the type of structures and actives on the land. The remaining difficulty is deciding how significant a structure or activity is necessary for the land to be associated with an establishment type. For example, it would not be realistic to classify all land with telephone lines under telephone communications; however, land with more important telephone communication facilities may be classified here.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Transportation, communication, information, and utilities

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Establishments in this subcategory produce equipment for transporting people and goods. Although transportation equipment is a type of machinery, assembly tends to be distinct from the production processes common in the machinery manufacturing, so these establishments are classified separately. Manufacturers of motor vehicle equipment used for non-transporting purposes (e.g., agriculture, construction, or materials handling) are classified elsewhere according the type and use of the equipment.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Transportation equipment, automobiles, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Activities associated with parking or storing of automobiles.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Vehicular parking, storage, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments are responsible for the construction of water mains, sewers, drains, gas mains, natural gas pumping stations, and gas and oil pipelines. Also included are well drilling contractors that drill, tap, and cap water wells, or that provide geothermal drilling.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Water, sewer, and pipeline construction

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This subcategory comprises public and private utility establishments that offer drinking water, water treatment, water supply, irrigation, steam supply, or hot or cool air supply.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Water, steam, air conditioning supply

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Activities primarily associated with linear features, such as pipelines, water channels, etc., located in easements and point features, such as air vents, pumping stations, piping junctions, etc., that may or may not be located in easements.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Water storing, pumping, or piping

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Establishments in this category manufacture wood and paper products, such as lumber, furniture, wood building products, mobile homes, and paper products. Some perform related services, such as printing and bookbinding. Subcategories reflect product distinctions.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Wood, paper, and printing products

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: This was a traditional planning category that is fast falling out of use. Many manufactured home developments are configured as zero lot line developments, townhouses are a form of zero lot line housing, and to further confuse the usage, former row houses are also used as barracks, group housing, or farm housing. Avoid this category if possible, but it is provided here for compatibility with many existing land-use databases that have this description.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Zero lot line, row houses, etc.

rdf:Description.dc:source: Land-Based Classification Standards American Planning Association http://www.planning.org/lbcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: These establishments preserve and exhibit live plant and animal life displays, including those in natural areas or settings (as in the case of national parks).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Zoos, botanical gardens, arboreta, etc.
